Hi there, philippe

On 11-Sep-02, you said:

pb> A general question about making a GUI. I'm wanted to know the best GUI for
pb> making a gadtools GUI and also If It's possible with Amiblitz to use a Gui
pb> maker for MUI and add the code in amiblitz, the same with other kind of GUI
pb> if It's possible.

It ispossible to use an MUI builder for Blitz, but you have to do a fair amount
of cleaning up afterwards. Also, the builders use MUI directly meaning that the
advantages of using the EFMUILib commands (and in some cases there are
advantages) are lost.

After a lot of work with MUI in Blitz, I've found the best approach is to do it
by hand. That way, you have more control, and in the long run, it tends to be
faster.

As an aside - be VERY careful when using MUI. Keep a close watch especially on
MUI object numbers, and make sure that you don't duplicate them. The debugger
won't catch th errors, and you'll crash - a lot. I find the best approach is to
assign a group of object numbers to each section of the GUI (enough so that
you'll have spare), and add a comment at the start of each section listing the
object numbers already used.

